+# GH-58 Deployment Evidence — Audiobookshelf on Pi5
+
+**Date:** 2026-07-20
+**Service:** Audiobookshelf (container `audiobookshelf`, host Pi5)
+**Scope:** GH-58 — reproducible Docker service, empty local test library.
+Excludes NFS, reverse proxy/TLS, Keycloak, production media.
+
+## Source of Truth
+- Compose: `pi/compose/audiobookshelf.yml` (merged via PR #63, healthcheck fix PR #65)
+- Architecture doc: `docs/AUDIOBOOKSHELF.md`
+
+## Deployment
+- Deployed on Pi5 at `/home/michael/audiobookshelf/docker-compose.yml`
+- Persistent bind mounts:
+  - `/mnt/hardDrive/docker/audiobookshelf/config` -> `/config`
+  - `/mnt/hardDrive/docker/audiobookshelf/metadata` -> `/metadata`
+- Image: `ghcr.io/advplyr/audiobookshelf@sha256:1eef6716183c52abafe5405e7d6be8390248ecd59c7488c44af871757ac8fc4d` (arm64, pinned)
+
+## Acceptance Criteria — Verified
+| Criterion | Result |
+|-----------|--------|
+| Container starts & reaches `healthy` | OK `Up ... (healthy)`, healthcheck `http://localhost:80/` returns 200 |
+| No host port exposed (internal-only) | OK `PortBindings: {}`, only `80/tcp` on internal bridge network |
+| Data persists across restart | OK `absdatabase.sqlite` + `migrations/` survive `docker restart` |
+| Resource limits enforced | OK MemLimit=512MB, NanoCpus=1.0, `no-new-privileges:true` |
+| Reproducible (pinned image, versioned compose) | OK Compose committed to Architecture repo |
+| GH-58 scope respected (no NFS/proxy/keycloak) | OK no NFS mounts, no proxy labels, no OIDC |
+
+## Fixes Applied During Deployment
+- **PR #63** deployed the initial compose but had a broken healthcheck:
+  probed `http://localhost:13378/health` — wrong port (app listens on `:80`)
+  and wrong path (`/health` returns 404; `/` returns 200). Container stuck `unhealthy`.
+- **PR #65** corrected healthcheck to `http://localhost:80/` and `expose: "80"`.
+  After redeploy, container reached `healthy`.
+- Local bind target dirs (`/mnt/hardDrive/docker/audiobookshelf/{config,metadata}`)
+  were created on the Pi (missing initially -> mount error).
+
+## Status
+GH-58 deployment complete and verified. Ready for GH-60 (OIDC) and a
+later child issue for `/audiobooks` NFS bind (section 7 of AUDIOBOOKSHELF.md).
